Results\: Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching. 32471eca-b4e1-4bfd-99e6-5ed5109e1cd3.description=
 Purpose

This workflow will drop the database specified by the deployment target.


 Description

This workflow drops a database specified by the deployment target.


 Dependencies

This workflow requires a database be created on an instance.



 Additional Documentation

Note that if a deployment of this workflow is created with a single target (database to drop) then after the workflow has finished execution the deployment will no longer exist. This is because the database that the deployment was pointing to no longer exists. To circumvent this problem use a smart group when creating a deployment.

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the RESOURCES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    Database Name - Name of the database which needs to be removed from the DMA environment.
    Database.Name - No description
    Instance Name - Name of the instance to which the database (the one that is to be deleted from the DMA environment) belongs to.
    Instance.Name - No description
    Server.Name - No description

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
    Instance Password - Optional - The Windows account password that will be performing the database drop.

Instance Password - Optional - The Windows account password that will be performing the database drop. Database.Name - No description host - Target to run this command against password - Login information for host username - Login information for host protocol - ssh/wmi timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen. Results\: Blank - An Empty String Database Name - Name of the MS SQL database that needs to be deleted. The value of this variable is "YES" Instance Account - The Windows account that will be performing the database drop. Instance Password - The password of the Windows account that will be performing the database drop. Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.
